.TH "knav_queue_open" 9 "knav_queue_open" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
knav_queue_open \- open a hardware queue
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" knav_queue_open
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "unsigned id "  ","
.BI "unsigned flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
- name to give the queue handle
.IP "id" 12
- desired queue number if any or specifes the type
of queue
.IP "flags" 12
- the following flags are applicable to queues:
KNAV_QUEUE_SHARED - allow the queue to be shared. Queues are
exclusive by default.
Subsequent attempts to open a shared queue should
also have this flag.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns a handle to the open hardware queue if successful. Use \fBIS_ERR\fP
to check the returned value for error codes.
